            "body": "> vim.system() appears to detect the exit/crash more reliably in my testing, but it is not a good replacement here because it does not launch/show this Windows GUI app the same way jobstart() does\n\nI suspect this hide field is why vim.system doesn't open the gui like jobstart.  \n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/36293#issuecomment-3448676928\n\nI think we should look into making the change I recommend it that comment where we set that hide field to false on windows. If I remember right, there was some extra weirdness though and I never finished investigating it since the relevant issue ended up getting merged.\n\n(Side-note the solution we went with in that referenced issue actually has a weird bug where for some reason \"open\" only opens file explorer once per path and I've been meaning to create a new issue for it. I should probably go do that while Im thinking of it lol)\n\nNote: on my phone so may edit this message with more details in a minute ",
